# header_checks filtering rules
# See `man 5 header_checks`, or http://www.postfix.org/header_checks.5.html

# Log the subject line of every message in /var/log/maillog

/^Subject: / WARN

# Bypass SpamAassasin for some trusted senders or recipients

/^To:.*ifttt-mail@domain.example.*/ FILTER local:
/^From:.*autogenerated@blocklist.de.*/ FILTER local:
/^From:.*notifications@github.com.*/ FILTER local:

# Custom rejections based on various message headers

/^From:.*annoyingspammer.com/ REJECT 5.7.1 Your mail is not welcome here
/^To: heavilyspammed@domain.example/ REJECT 5.1.1 No such user
/^Received:.*heavilyspammed@domain.example/ REJECT 5.1.1 No such user
/^Reply-To: careteam@care.com/ REJECT 5.1.1 Invalid recipient, please confirm your users email addresses before sending messages
/^X-PHP-Originating-Script: 1001:Sendmail.php/ REJECT 5.7.1 Message smells like poo, flushing
